WEBVTT

00:28.029 --> 00:31.950
♪♪ (rock: upbeat)

01:04.232 --> 01:09.320
♪♪ (jazz)

01:53.782 --> 01:55.492
(engine revving)

01:55.575 --> 01:58.578
- (shouting)
- (cans rattling)

02:23.770 --> 02:26.773
(shouting continues)

03:00.974 --> 03:03.977
(chattering, indistinct)

03:06.479 --> 03:09.482
(shouting continues)

03:22.287 --> 03:25.123
- It's too long. Nice to see you again.
- Cheerio.

03:54.652 --> 03:57.864
(shouting continues)

04:05.496 --> 04:07.832
(shouting continues)

04:13.421 --> 04:16.382
- Give me your money. Do it!
- (laughs)

04:19.385 --> 04:21.053
WOMAN: Thank you.

04:45.495 --> 04:48.164
- Blue 439.
- (radio: static)

04:48.247 --> 04:50.124
Blue 439. Over.

04:50.208 --> 04:53.419
DISPATCHER:
<i>Blue 439. Go ahead, please. Over.</i>

04:53.503 --> 04:56.422
Phone Weston 0219.
Tell 'em I'm on my way, will you?

04:56.506 --> 04:58.508
DISPATCHER: <i>Roger. Wilco. Stand by.</i>

05:09.435 --> 05:10.979
(parking brake sets)

05:35.628 --> 05:37.505
- Hello, love.
- Hello.

05:47.807 --> 05:50.810
(chattering)

05:55.440 --> 05:56.941
Here.

06:00.319 --> 06:02.321
- Get that stuff developed, will you?
- Yeah.

06:03.281 --> 06:04.741
Right away.

06:19.547 --> 06:21.090
Here I am.

06:26.262 --> 06:28.181
Ready?

06:29.474 --> 06:31.809
I've been ready for nearly an hour.

06:31.893 --> 06:33.686
Good.

06:33.770 --> 06:36.647
I'm catching a plane for Paris
at 11:00, so I can't -

06:36.731 --> 06:38.316
Can't what?

06:39.400 --> 06:41.444
It doesn't matter.

06:41.527 --> 06:44.363
(flash popping)

06:47.325 --> 06:50.328
- Who the hell were you with last night?
- (scoffs)

06:51.704 --> 06:53.414
Reg?

06:58.002 --> 06:59.712
(shade pulls up)

07:33.121 --> 07:35.331
Reg, let's have some noise, can you?

07:39.919 --> 07:44.590
♪♪ (record player: blues jazz)

07:44.674 --> 07:47.218
- Right.
- (camera winds)

07:47.301 --> 07:49.720
- That's good. That's good. Hold that.
- (shutter clicking)

07:52.723 --> 07:56.894
(shutter continues clicking)

08:19.625 --> 08:23.087
(shutter continues clicking)

08:23.171 --> 08:24.630
Reg?

08:29.677 --> 08:32.554
♪♪ (fades)

08:33.556 --> 08:36.767
♪♪ (speakers: jazz)

08:36.851 --> 08:40.188
Give it to me now. Come on. That's good.

08:42.857 --> 08:45.151
Hunch. Hunch more.

08:45.234 --> 08:46.819
That's good.

08:48.946 --> 08:51.949
That's good.
And the hair back. And the hair back.

08:53.492 --> 08:55.494
Come on. That's great.
That's great! That's good. Good.

08:55.578 --> 08:58.039
Come on. More of that.
Now really give it to me.

09:00.625 --> 09:04.086
That's good. As fast as you can.
Give it to me. Come on. Right forward.

09:04.170 --> 09:06.839
Good. That's good.
Now this side. Lean right forward.

09:06.923 --> 09:10.593
Hand up. Hand up. That's great.
Just touch the face. Just touch the face.

09:10.676 --> 09:14.013
That's very good. And again.
Around this way. Touch the face again.

09:14.096 --> 09:17.391
- (shutter clicks)
- Good. Now the hair. Marvelous. That's great.

09:17.475 --> 09:20.102
Good. Yes, the hair. Much more. Much more.

09:20.811 --> 09:24.440
Good. That's great. Yes, that's great.
That's good. Yes. Go on. And again.

09:25.316 --> 09:27.318
Oh, hold that, with the hair. Again.

09:27.401 --> 09:29.028
- (shutter continues clicking)
- Good.

09:30.071 --> 09:32.323
Okay, Reg, flip me.

09:32.406 --> 09:33.824
On your back.

09:33.908 --> 09:35.576
On your back. Go on.

09:37.787 --> 09:40.122
Yes. Now, really give it. Come on.

09:40.206 --> 09:43.042
- (shutter continues clicking)
- Come on. Work, work, work!

09:43.668 --> 09:47.755
Great. Great. And again. Go on.
Back. Back. Arms up. Arms up.

09:47.838 --> 09:50.174
Stretch yourself. Amazing. Great.

09:50.258 --> 09:52.551
And again. Go on. Go, go.

09:57.723 --> 09:59.225
Great.

09:59.308 --> 10:02.353
That's it! Keep it up! Lovely!

10:02.436 --> 10:05.022
Yeah, make it come. Great!

10:05.106 --> 10:07.108
No. No. Head up, head up.

10:08.859 --> 10:10.903
- For me, love. For me.
- (shutter continues clicking)

10:10.987 --> 10:12.905
Now! Now! Yes!

10:12.989 --> 10:14.782
Yes! Yes!

10:16.367 --> 10:19.370
♪♪ (jazz continues)

10:30.423 --> 10:32.717
(phone ringing)

10:35.678 --> 10:38.848
♪♪ (ends)

10:38.931 --> 10:40.766
REG: Hello.

10:40.850 --> 10:42.476
Yeah, hold on.

10:44.020 --> 10:45.604
It's Peter.

10:46.814 --> 10:48.774
Hello?

10:48.858 --> 10:51.277
Huh? Yes.

10:52.403 --> 10:54.447
Yes.

10:54.530 --> 10:56.907
Yeah, I've got it somewhere.
I know I have.

10:58.034 --> 11:00.286
Huh? Yeah, hold on.

11:00.995 --> 11:04.832
Reg, take down the address of
that bloody junk shop, would you?

11:36.864 --> 11:38.866
Why, they're fabulous. Go on.

11:40.201 --> 11:41.786
Yes.

11:44.288 --> 11:46.457
Yes. Great.

11:47.625 --> 11:49.668
Here, you can burn that lot.

11:50.878 --> 11:53.172
(water sloshing, draining)

11:58.469 --> 12:00.679
♪♪ (speakers: jazz)

12:05.226 --> 12:08.646
♪♪ (jazz continues, louder)

12:10.648 --> 12:13.234
(loud whistle)

12:13.317 --> 12:14.819
Reg!

12:16.612 --> 12:19.156
- Get the birds down, will you?
- REG: Okay.

13:03.826 --> 13:07.079
Oi! No chewing gum. Get rid of it.

13:07.997 --> 13:10.082
And not on my floor.

13:11.000 --> 13:13.002
You. Arm down.

13:14.086 --> 13:15.921
Right.

13:16.005 --> 13:17.715
REG: Six, yeah.

13:23.762 --> 13:26.098
- (shutter clicks)
- Terrible.

13:28.684 --> 13:31.937
How about the leg
a little further forward?

13:33.564 --> 13:35.274
Put the head up.

13:45.159 --> 13:47.828
Just go. Mouth open. Yes, good.

13:47.912 --> 13:50.039
Good.

13:51.457 --> 13:54.043
(shutter continues clicking)

14:16.106 --> 14:18.484
No, you're - Start again.
Start again. Rethink it.

14:18.567 --> 14:20.236
Rethink it.

14:24.532 --> 14:26.283
Stripes, let the dress just fall down.

14:26.367 --> 14:28.827
Absolutely fall. Keep the stripes steady.
It's very important to keep -

14:28.911 --> 14:31.038
Just let your arms go up and down.

14:31.121 --> 14:34.291
Yes! Very tasty.
Yes, I like it, I like it. Go on.

14:35.709 --> 14:37.086
Yeah.

14:37.169 --> 14:38.921
All right, change position.

14:43.509 --> 14:44.885
Yup.

14:45.761 --> 14:48.472
(whistles) Wake up!

14:49.515 --> 14:51.141
(shutter continues clicking)

14:51.225 --> 14:54.562
Now, you can thank your lucky stars
you're working with me, can't you?

14:54.645 --> 14:57.189
- All right, one more.
- (shutter continues clicking)

14:57.273 --> 14:59.275
And a smile now. Come on.

15:00.317 --> 15:02.236
Smile.

15:02.319 --> 15:04.488
Smile!

15:04.572 --> 15:06.740
(shutter continues clicking)

15:09.285 --> 15:10.703
God.

15:12.871 --> 15:14.331
(clears throat)

15:16.417 --> 15:18.419
I asked you to smile.

15:19.628 --> 15:21.088
What's the matter?

15:22.506 --> 15:24.717
Have you forgotten what a smile is?

15:24.800 --> 15:26.802
(shouts) Eh?

15:34.977 --> 15:37.688
All right, you're all tired now.
Go on, relax.

15:39.398 --> 15:42.192
I can't see your eyeballs anymore.
They're just slits.

15:42.276 --> 15:45.195
- ♪♪ (pop: man singing)
- Go on.

15:46.071 --> 15:47.948
Close your eyes.

15:49.116 --> 15:50.909
Close your eyes.

15:50.993 --> 15:53.203
♪♪ (pop continues)

15:55.456 --> 15:57.458
And stay like that.

15:59.043 --> 16:00.669
It's good for you.

16:07.259 --> 16:10.179
<i>♪ Sometimes you really dig a girl ♪</i>

16:10.262 --> 16:12.014
<i>♪ The moment you kiss her ♪</i>

16:12.097 --> 16:16.143
<i>♪ And you get distracted
by her older sister ♪</i>

16:16.226 --> 16:19.146
<i>♪ Then in walks her father
and takes you a line ♪</i>

16:19.229 --> 16:20.856
Close your eyes.

17:05.818 --> 17:08.362
That must be five or six years old.

17:13.367 --> 17:16.869
They don't mean anything
when I do them. Just a mess.

17:19.289 --> 17:23.042
Afterwards I find something to hang on to.

17:23.127 --> 17:26.255
Like that... Like that leg.

17:30.592 --> 17:32.970
Then it sorts itself out...

17:33.053 --> 17:34.847
and adds up.

17:37.725 --> 17:40.728
It's like finding a clue in a detective story.

17:44.231 --> 17:47.234
Don't ask me about this one.
I don't know yet.

17:48.819 --> 17:51.405
- Can I buy it?
- No.

17:53.073 --> 17:55.075
Will you give it to me?

18:22.144 --> 18:25.397
- (bottle cap opens)
- (cap clatters on countertop)

18:31.862 --> 18:33.489
WOMAN: There.

18:33.572 --> 18:35.199
Mmm. Thanks.

18:39.912 --> 18:41.872
Tight-faced bastard.

18:41.955 --> 18:44.958
He won't sell me
one of his crappy paintings!

18:52.925 --> 18:54.343
Mmm.

18:56.595 --> 18:59.014
I'll creep down one night
and knock it off.

18:59.097 --> 19:01.016
(woman chuckles)

19:10.400 --> 19:12.820
Mmm, don't stop. It's lovely.

19:16.198 --> 19:18.617
- You look tired.
- Mmm.

19:18.700 --> 19:21.203
I've been all night in a doss house.

19:53.527 --> 19:56.655
They say they've been asked to come here.

19:56.738 --> 19:58.198
Not by me.

19:58.282 --> 20:01.493
Well, we weren't exactly asked.

20:03.203 --> 20:05.247
Sorry. I'm busy.

20:05.330 --> 20:08.750
They're printing some snaps for me upstairs.
Go and fetch 'em.

20:13.630 --> 20:16.466
Couldn't you give us
just a couple of minutes?

20:17.009 --> 20:18.468
A couple of minutes?

20:18.552 --> 20:21.638
I haven't even got a couple of minutes
to have my appendix out.

20:37.487 --> 20:38.947
♪♪ (pop)

20:39.031 --> 20:41.491
<i>♪ You're in a whole lot of trouble
Didn't know you had a double ♪</i>

20:41.575 --> 20:44.912
<i>♪ Dab my feet in the water
Thought you was an only daughter ♪</i>

20:44.995 --> 20:46.747
<i>♪ Seen a whole lot of trouble ♪</i>

20:46.830 --> 20:49.249
<i>♪ Wow, Jubilee ♪</i>

20:49.333 --> 20:51.501
♪♪ (pop continues)

20:51.585 --> 20:53.921
- When can we come then?
- Don't.

20:57.549 --> 20:59.468
The others still waiting
with their eyes shut?

20:59.551 --> 21:02.846
Yes, they're waiting,
but their eyes are open.

21:02.930 --> 21:05.015
Good.

21:05.098 --> 21:07.267
Then tell them to shut 'em again.

21:17.235 --> 21:19.821
Get rid of that bag. It's diabolical.

21:21.239 --> 21:23.408
(engine starts)

21:24.534 --> 21:26.870
Can we come back this afternoon?

21:35.796 --> 21:38.715
♪♪ (radio: pop)

21:38.799 --> 21:40.801
(mouthing words)

21:45.681 --> 21:47.307
(horn honks)

22:38.108 --> 22:39.526
(parking brake sets)

22:47.617 --> 22:49.494
(bell jingling)

23:15.520 --> 23:18.690
- What do you want?
- Just looking around.

23:18.774 --> 23:21.401
There are no cheap bargains here.
You're wasting your time.

23:22.402 --> 23:24.446
Well, I'll just have a look.

23:26.156 --> 23:29.159
- What are you lookin' for?
- Pictures.

23:29.868 --> 23:31.578
No pictures.

23:34.873 --> 23:36.500
(coughing)

23:36.583 --> 23:38.543
What kind of pictures?

23:42.255 --> 23:43.715
Landscapes.

23:43.799 --> 23:45.801
Sorry. No landscapes.

23:56.728 --> 23:58.939
CLERK: Sold. All sold.

24:03.110 --> 24:06.363
- You the owner?
- No. The owner is out.

24:09.116 --> 24:10.992
Expecting him?

24:13.120 --> 24:15.288
(blowing)

24:20.919 --> 24:22.629
(bell jingling)

24:51.533 --> 24:54.286
(shutter clicking)

26:03.271 --> 26:05.440
(shutter clicking)

26:58.952 --> 27:00.370
(exhales)

27:37.032 --> 27:39.367
(woman sighs, laughs)

28:00.347 --> 28:02.724
(shutter clicking)

29:12.419 --> 29:15.046
(shutter clicking)

29:22.470 --> 29:25.473
(shutter continues clicking)

30:18.276 --> 30:19.903
WOMAN: What are you doing?

30:19.986 --> 30:22.280
Stop it! Stop it!

30:22.363 --> 30:25.325
Give me those pictures.
You can't photograph people like that.

30:25.408 --> 30:28.328
Who says I can't? I'm only doing my job.

30:28.411 --> 30:32.499
Some people are bullfighters.
Some people are politicians.

30:32.582 --> 30:34.250
I'm a photographer.

30:35.585 --> 30:39.130
This is a public place.
Everyone has the right to be left in peace.

30:41.299 --> 30:43.635
It's not my fault if there's no peace.

30:45.178 --> 30:48.181
You know, most girls would
pay me to photograph them.

30:50.058 --> 30:51.726
I'll pay you.

30:52.560 --> 30:54.771
I overcharge.

30:54.854 --> 30:57.273
There are other things I want on the reel.

31:11.329 --> 31:13.498
What do we do then?

31:13.581 --> 31:15.959
I'll send you the photographs.

31:16.042 --> 31:17.835
No, I want them now.

31:25.176 --> 31:27.637
Ow! What's the rush?

31:35.353 --> 31:38.189
Don't let's spoil everything.
We've only just met.

31:42.026 --> 31:43.861
(sighs)

31:50.743 --> 31:53.371
No, we haven't met. You've never seen me.

32:34.037 --> 32:37.040
♪♪ (record player: jazz guitar)

32:56.267 --> 32:59.270
♪♪ (jazz guitar continues)

33:03.066 --> 33:04.651
- Hello.
- Hello.

33:04.734 --> 33:06.361
♪♪ (ends)

33:06.444 --> 33:09.822
- Uh, my agent saw you about the shop.
- Did he?

33:10.823 --> 33:14.035
He's a man with a cigar.
Throws ash everywhere.

33:14.994 --> 33:17.246
I expect I remember him.

33:18.373 --> 33:21.292
I probably asked for too much money.

33:21.376 --> 33:23.878
Money's always a problem, isn't it?

33:27.131 --> 33:29.050
Tell him to come back.

33:29.133 --> 33:32.136
♪♪ (record player: jazz, piano)

33:33.179 --> 33:34.722
Why are you selling?

33:35.723 --> 33:37.517
♪♪ (stops)

33:41.771 --> 33:44.399
I'd like to try something different,

33:44.482 --> 33:46.401
get off somewhere.

33:46.484 --> 33:48.820
I'm fed up with antiques.

33:50.321 --> 33:53.574
- Get off where?
- To Nepal.

33:55.326 --> 33:58.079
Nepal is all antiques.

33:58.162 --> 33:59.956
- Is it?
- Mm-hmm.

34:01.874 --> 34:05.086
Perhaps I'd better try Morocco.

34:15.346 --> 34:16.806
- How much?
- What?

34:16.889 --> 34:18.349
The propeller.

34:21.853 --> 34:24.813
You can have it for... eight pounds.

34:24.897 --> 34:27.150
Right. You're in business.
Have you got a van?

34:27.233 --> 34:29.068
You can't take it now.

34:29.152 --> 34:32.237
I must. I must.

34:32.321 --> 34:34.489
- I can't live without it.
- Hard luck.

34:34.574 --> 34:37.952
That'll teach you to fall in love
with heavy things on Saturday morning.

34:49.547 --> 34:51.966
- Is that it?
- That's it.

34:57.263 --> 35:00.391
You can't treat it like that.
It's not a delivery van.

35:00.475 --> 35:02.018
Who cares?

35:02.101 --> 35:05.271
Leave it to me. Something will turn up.

35:06.481 --> 35:09.108
Yes. All right.
But it'd better turn up today.

35:12.570 --> 35:14.071
Oi!

35:18.993 --> 35:20.995
(engine starts)

35:57.907 --> 35:59.826
Blue 439. Blue 439. Over.

35:59.909 --> 36:01.244
(radio: static)

36:01.327 --> 36:04.622
DISPATCHER (on radio):
<i>Blue 439. Go ahead, please. Over.</i>

36:04.705 --> 36:06.457
Hello, this is, uh...

36:06.541 --> 36:10.711
Get me Flaxman double 2-4-9.
Mr. Walker. Mr. Peter Walker.

36:10.795 --> 36:14.674
Tell him I've seen the junk shop. It's a bit
pricey, but I think the kid'll come down.

36:14.757 --> 36:18.594
Let him ring her right away.
Then nobody else will get it.

36:18.678 --> 36:20.513
(radio: static)

36:20.596 --> 36:22.974
DISPATCHER: <i>Roger. Wilco. Stand by.</i>

36:28.688 --> 36:32.358
DISPATCHER: <i>Blue 439. Blue 439. Over.</i>

36:32.441 --> 36:35.152
Blue 439. Blue 439. Go ahead, Echo.

36:35.236 --> 36:39.198
<i>Blue 439. Message passed and understood.
Your caller doesn't like it. Over.</i>

36:39.282 --> 36:41.617
Tell him to get stuffed.

36:41.701 --> 36:44.495
What about all the buildings
going up around the place?

36:44.579 --> 36:47.915
Already there are queers
and poodles in the area.

36:49.333 --> 36:51.878
I saw some in the couple of minutes
I was there.

36:51.961 --> 36:54.213
It'll go like a bomb. Over.

36:54.297 --> 36:57.258
<i>Blue 439, what is in the area? Over.</i>

36:57.341 --> 37:00.803
- Forget it. Over.
<i>- Roger. Wilco. Standing by.</i>

37:28.664 --> 37:30.541
You want to use the lot?

37:41.844 --> 37:43.346
PHOTOGRAPHER: Don't you like 'em?

37:44.096 --> 37:45.640
MAN: They're great.

37:52.188 --> 37:53.773
We'll use three or four.

37:55.232 --> 37:57.193
Spread through the book?

37:57.276 --> 37:59.487
No. All together.

37:59.570 --> 38:01.072
Yeah.

38:05.534 --> 38:07.370
- And a pint.
- Yes, sir.

38:10.164 --> 38:12.458
- Which one last?
- None of this lot.

38:12.541 --> 38:15.753
I've got something fab for the end.
In a park.

38:15.836 --> 38:18.422
I only took them this morning.
You'll get them later on today.

38:18.506 --> 38:21.258
It's very... peaceful, very still.

38:22.218 --> 38:26.681
The rest of the book'll be pretty violent,
so I think it's best to end it like that. Hmm?

38:26.764 --> 38:28.349
MAN: Yes.

38:28.432 --> 38:30.601
That's best.

38:30.685 --> 38:32.311
Rings truer.

38:47.493 --> 38:49.996
I've gone off London this week.

38:50.079 --> 38:51.580
Why?

38:55.001 --> 38:57.211
Doesn't do anything for me.

38:57.294 --> 39:00.256
(chuckles) Yeah.

39:00.339 --> 39:02.591
- I've knocked up a few captions.
- Yeah?

39:14.895 --> 39:17.106
I'm fed up with those bloody bitches.

39:17.940 --> 39:20.067
Wish I had tons of money.

39:20.151 --> 39:22.236
Then I'd be free.

39:22.319 --> 39:23.863
Free to do what?

39:25.239 --> 39:26.615
Free like him?

39:36.417 --> 39:38.127
Someone we know?

39:50.014 --> 39:51.766
(car trunk closes)

39:53.809 --> 39:56.812
(men chattering in foreign language)

40:35.267 --> 40:36.727
(engine starts)

40:40.606 --> 40:43.025
(horn honking)

40:57.873 --> 41:00.251
(horn honking)

41:17.059 --> 41:18.602
Hello?

41:18.686 --> 41:20.312
That'll be all right.

41:49.967 --> 41:51.594
- (engine off)
- (parking brake sets)

41:52.469 --> 41:54.597
MAN (on radio, faint): <i>Good afternoon.</i>

41:57.433 --> 42:01.437
<i>Let me hand it over to J.H. Goodman.</i>
(continues, indistinct)

42:03.230 --> 42:05.482
MAN #2: <i>Thank you, Freddy, thank you.</i>

42:05.566 --> 42:10.571
(horn blaring)

42:14.033 --> 42:17.536
(radio: man continues, faint, indistinct)

42:51.195 --> 42:53.739
Hello. Could you get me
Frobisher 3-double-2-9, please?

42:53.822 --> 42:55.449
I've only got a sixpence.

42:56.450 --> 42:59.453
(coughs) Park 1296.

43:06.543 --> 43:07.920
Hello. It's me.

43:09.046 --> 43:12.091
Weren't you supposed to be
going off to, um, Hurley?

43:13.008 --> 43:14.593
Hmm?

43:15.844 --> 43:18.514
Listen. Stay where you are.

43:18.597 --> 43:20.849
Call me soon at home. Mmm.

43:35.281 --> 43:39.368
(panting) I've come -
I've come for the photographs.

43:41.495 --> 43:43.580
How did you manage to find me?

43:46.125 --> 43:47.960
Do you live here?

43:49.712 --> 43:51.005
Mmm.

44:34.715 --> 44:38.385
- (clicks)
- ♪♪ (record player: soft jazz)

44:39.511 --> 44:41.221
- (clicks)
- Drink?

44:53.150 --> 44:56.070
What's so important
about my bloody pictures?

44:57.613 --> 44:59.406
That's my business.

45:08.415 --> 45:10.709
♪♪ (soft jazz continues)

45:11.835 --> 45:14.922
The light was very beautiful
in the park this morning.

45:15.005 --> 45:17.007
Those shots should be very good.

45:18.092 --> 45:19.718
Anyway, I need them.

45:24.431 --> 45:28.268
My private life's already in a mess.
It would be a disaster if...

45:30.687 --> 45:32.106
So what?

45:34.400 --> 45:37.736
Nothing like a little disaster
for sorting things out.

45:48.163 --> 45:50.666
Have you ever done any modeling?

45:50.749 --> 45:52.751
Fashion stuff, I mean.

45:54.169 --> 45:55.921
You've got it.

46:15.232 --> 46:16.817
Hold that.

46:20.737 --> 46:23.449
Not many girls can stand as well as that.

46:24.324 --> 46:26.452
No, thanks. I'm in a hurry.

46:28.871 --> 46:31.081
You'll get your pictures.

46:31.165 --> 46:32.708
I promise.

46:32.791 --> 46:34.835
I always keep my word.

46:36.211 --> 46:37.754
Come here.

46:39.756 --> 46:41.508
Show me how you sit.

46:42.885 --> 46:44.553
(exhales)

46:50.434 --> 46:53.437
(phone ringing)

46:58.901 --> 47:02.154
(ringing continues)

47:10.704 --> 47:12.956
Ooh. (grunts) Who is it?

47:15.125 --> 47:18.128
Oh, yes, that's right. Hold on a second.

47:21.924 --> 47:23.759
Is it for me?

47:28.972 --> 47:30.474
It's my wife.

47:32.017 --> 47:34.728
Why should I speak to her?

47:38.857 --> 47:41.860
Sorry, love.
The bird I'm with won't talk to you.

48:15.561 --> 48:17.563
She isn't my wife, really.

48:18.480 --> 48:20.482
We just have some kids.

48:22.276 --> 48:24.611
No. No kids.

48:24.695 --> 48:26.446
Not even kids.

48:28.448 --> 48:32.244
Sometimes though, it -
it feels as if we had kids.

48:35.247 --> 48:37.249
She isn't beautiful, she's...

48:38.667 --> 48:40.711
easy to live with.

48:44.965 --> 48:46.592
No, she isn't.

48:47.926 --> 48:49.845
That's why I don't live with her.

48:49.928 --> 48:52.931
♪♪ (soft jazz continues)

49:15.579 --> 49:18.165
♪♪ (ends)

49:18.248 --> 49:20.751
But even with beautiful girls, you -

49:20.834 --> 49:22.961
you look at them and that's that.

49:24.296 --> 49:26.965
That's why they always end up, uh...

49:29.676 --> 49:32.137
And I'm stuck with them all day long.

49:35.307 --> 49:37.517
It would be the same with men.

49:38.602 --> 49:41.396
♪♪ (record player: jazz, new song)

49:42.606 --> 49:44.191
Have a listen to this.

49:44.274 --> 49:46.318
♪♪ (volume increases)

49:46.401 --> 49:49.404
♪♪ (jazz: upbeat)

49:55.160 --> 49:59.039
♪♪ (jazz continues)

49:59.122 --> 50:01.583
No, keep still. Keep still.

50:01.667 --> 50:04.670
- Listen. Keep still.
- ♪♪ (jazz continues)

50:09.883 --> 50:12.010
You can smoke, if you like.

50:15.681 --> 50:17.349
Slowly. Slowly.

50:18.225 --> 50:19.976
Against the beat.

50:28.777 --> 50:31.238
♪♪ (jazz continues)

50:31.321 --> 50:33.115
That's it.

50:53.760 --> 50:56.054
(laughs)

51:12.738 --> 51:14.406
(gasps)

51:14.489 --> 51:18.243
(laughs) I can't stand it.
I'm nervous enough as it is.

51:23.498 --> 51:25.667
Can I have some water?

51:25.751 --> 51:27.127
(grunts)

51:30.464 --> 51:32.090
♪♪ (stops)

52:11.379 --> 52:13.715
And I'm not a fool, love.

52:22.724 --> 52:25.101
Can I have the photographs?

52:25.185 --> 52:27.187
Of course.

52:27.270 --> 52:28.897
Later.

52:32.317 --> 52:34.528
Your boyfriend's a bit past it.

52:41.785 --> 52:43.954
Why don't you say what you want?

53:16.611 --> 53:18.613
Get dressed.

53:23.285 --> 53:25.620
I'll cut out the negatives you want.

53:48.518 --> 53:52.522
♪♪ (record player: soft jazz, slow tempo)

55:19.025 --> 55:21.277
(doorbell buzzes)

55:22.529 --> 55:24.155
They'll go.

55:25.073 --> 55:27.075
(doorbell continues buzzing)

55:27.158 --> 55:28.910
They're not going.

55:33.623 --> 55:35.500
Don't go.

55:47.846 --> 55:49.848
- Have you bought a propeller?
- What?

55:50.598 --> 55:53.309
You bought a propeller this morning, right?

55:53.393 --> 55:55.687
Oh, yes.

55:55.770 --> 55:58.398
You'll have to give us a hand with it.

56:14.330 --> 56:16.750
- All right?
- Fine, yeah.

56:21.379 --> 56:23.298
What's it for?

56:23.381 --> 56:25.884
Nothing. It's beautiful.

56:25.967 --> 56:30.138
If I had a big room like this,
I'd hang it from the ceiling like a fan.

56:31.347 --> 56:33.600
- Do you live on your own?
- No.

56:41.357 --> 56:44.444
Perhaps I'll put it there
like a piece of sculpture.

56:44.527 --> 56:47.447
It'll look good there.
It will break up the straight lines.

57:09.844 --> 57:11.846
- Are you going?
- It's late.

57:12.430 --> 57:14.390
Do I see you again?

57:14.849 --> 57:17.352
♪♪ (record player: soft jazz)

57:17.435 --> 57:20.897
Well, at least tell me your name
or your telephone number.

57:52.804 --> 57:54.305
Thank you.

58:05.108 --> 58:07.402
♪♪ (ends)

59:07.253 --> 59:09.589
(whirring quietly)

59:10.715 --> 59:12.217
(whirring stops)

59:37.033 --> 59:38.952
(liquid flowing)

01:00:15.530 --> 01:00:18.199
- (switch clicks)
- (fan blowing)

01:01:00.950 --> 01:01:02.452
(match strikes)

01:02:44.011 --> 01:02:48.015
♪♪ (record player: jazz)

01:03:13.332 --> 01:03:15.334
♪♪ (fades)

01:04:27.782 --> 01:04:28.991
(blowing)

01:06:25.107 --> 01:06:27.276
Hello? Knightsbridge 1239?

01:06:29.487 --> 01:06:30.905
What?

01:06:32.365 --> 01:06:34.325
No, I'm sorry.

01:08:02.121 --> 01:08:05.040
(wind rustling leaves)

01:09:17.488 --> 01:09:19.323
Ron?

01:09:19.406 --> 01:09:21.492
Something fantastic's happened.

01:09:21.575 --> 01:09:24.745
Those photographs in the park - fantastic.

01:09:25.787 --> 01:09:28.415
Somebody was trying to kill somebody else.

01:09:28.499 --> 01:09:30.334
I saved his life.

01:09:31.417 --> 01:09:33.504
Listen, Ron, there was a girl.

01:09:35.923 --> 01:09:37.800
Ron, will you listen?

01:09:37.883 --> 01:09:40.469
- What makes it so fantastic -
- (doorbell buzzes)

01:09:42.220 --> 01:09:44.974
Look, hang on, will you, Ron?
There's somebody at the door.

01:10:07.872 --> 01:10:09.373
He is home.

01:10:12.501 --> 01:10:14.503
You weren't expecting us, were you?

01:10:15.671 --> 01:10:17.006
No.

01:10:31.562 --> 01:10:33.856
Could you manage to make a cup
of coffee between you?

01:10:33.939 --> 01:10:37.818
I can make an Irish coffee, if you'd like.
(laughing)

01:10:42.823 --> 01:10:44.658
All right, come on.

01:10:44.742 --> 01:10:46.702
(laughing continues)

01:10:59.632 --> 01:11:01.467
- Is she always like that?
- Like what?

01:11:01.550 --> 01:11:03.177
Doesn't speak.

01:11:05.888 --> 01:11:07.932
What's your name?

01:11:09.016 --> 01:11:11.477
Ah, forget it. What's the use of a name?

01:11:13.354 --> 01:11:15.356
What do they call you in bed?

01:11:16.899 --> 01:11:18.984
I only go to bed to sleep.

01:11:38.212 --> 01:11:39.630
PHOTOGRAPHER: Hello.

01:11:44.259 --> 01:11:45.886
Hello.

01:11:52.101 --> 01:11:53.602
Psst.

01:11:54.269 --> 01:11:56.480
Look at all these clothes.

01:12:02.820 --> 01:12:04.488
Ooh.

01:12:05.614 --> 01:12:07.199
No.

01:12:09.827 --> 01:12:11.662
Hey, how 'bout this one?

01:12:11.745 --> 01:12:13.414
Put it on.

01:12:20.087 --> 01:12:21.338
(giggles)

01:12:29.847 --> 01:12:30.848
Oh.

01:12:34.852 --> 01:12:36.353
(gasps)

01:12:38.313 --> 01:12:40.524
What about you? Help yourself.

01:12:42.776 --> 01:12:45.195
- (tea kettle whistles)
- The coffee!

01:13:13.932 --> 01:13:15.768
- (grunts)
- (screams)

01:13:27.488 --> 01:13:30.324
(gasping)

01:13:30.407 --> 01:13:32.409
- (crying)
- Aaah!

01:13:32.493 --> 01:13:35.370
(screaming)

01:13:36.413 --> 01:13:38.123
- What's the matter?
- She's got a better figure than me!

01:13:38.207 --> 01:13:41.085
- Oh, it's not true.
- Oh, no!

01:13:41.168 --> 01:13:43.712
(screaming, laughing)

01:13:46.757 --> 01:13:49.384
Go on, whack her.
Go on. Give her a left hook.

01:13:49.468 --> 01:13:51.678
- (laughing)
- Put you in the ring together.

01:13:51.762 --> 01:13:54.264
Oh! Oh, no! (screams)

01:13:57.726 --> 01:13:58.852
(screams)

01:13:58.936 --> 01:14:01.313
Oh! Oh, no.

01:14:01.396 --> 01:14:04.983
(screams, laughs)

01:14:06.068 --> 01:14:08.779
(squealing, laughing)

01:14:12.032 --> 01:14:15.369
(laughing continues)

01:14:26.004 --> 01:14:28.090
(squealing)

01:14:31.844 --> 01:14:33.762
No! (laughing)

01:14:40.811 --> 01:14:42.146
Hold her legs.

01:14:43.397 --> 01:14:47.526
(laughing, screaming)

01:14:50.863 --> 01:14:53.949
(laughing continues)

01:14:56.618 --> 01:14:59.955
- Hold her legs!
- No! No, no!

01:15:00.038 --> 01:15:02.207
No! No!

01:15:02.291 --> 01:15:05.127
(screaming) No!

01:15:08.839 --> 01:15:10.174
(squeals)

01:15:13.844 --> 01:15:15.387
(squealing)

01:15:21.310 --> 01:15:23.103
Let go of me!

01:15:27.524 --> 01:15:29.693
(squealing)

01:15:38.577 --> 01:15:40.204
(Thomas laughing)

01:17:16.300 --> 01:17:17.968
Right, let's move. Out.

01:17:18.051 --> 01:17:19.678
You haven't taken any photos.

01:17:19.761 --> 01:17:22.389
No. Not now. I'm too whacked.

01:17:22.472 --> 01:17:24.099
It's your own faults.

01:17:37.821 --> 01:17:39.448
Tomorrow.

01:17:44.411 --> 01:17:45.912
Tomorrow!

01:19:02.447 --> 01:19:03.907
(shutter clicks)

01:19:09.788 --> 01:19:11.415
(shutter clicks)

